        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 7:09AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 709 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Friendship, or near
Preston, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Americus, Preston, Plains, Sumter, Friendship, Maddox, Croxton
Crossroads, Church Hill, and Dumas.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
